.TH oremind 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
oremind \- desktop self-observation reminder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B oremind
.RI [ OPTION ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B oremind
runs a small Linux desktop observer in the background.  It starts without a
main window, immediately shows an observation prompt, and then repeats at the
configured interval.
.PP
Each prompt asks for a short activity note and optional energy, mood, and
grounding scores.  The prompt can be submitted with Enter, cancelled with
Escape, or snoozed for 30 seconds with Control-S.  Empty activity text is
trimmed and not recorded.
.PP
By default records are stored in
.IR ~/.observer/observer.sqlite3 .
The storage path can also point at a directory, in which case daily text log
files are written instead.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase logging verbosity.  This option may be repeated.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Decrease logging verbosity.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit successfully.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-locale " " \fILOCALE\fR
Set the UI locale before translations are initialized.  Examples include
.BR en ,
.BR zh_CN ,
.BR zh_TW ,
.BR ja ,
.BR ko ,
.BR fr ,
and
.BR de .
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-theme " " \fITHEME\fR
Set the prompt theme.  Supported values are
.B light
and
.BR dark .
The default is
.BR dark .
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-opacity " " \fINUM\fR
Set the final dialog opacity as a percentage from
.B 0
to
.BR 100 .
The default is
.BR 75 .
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fINUM\fR
Set the normal prompt interval in minutes.  Fractional values are accepted.
An interval of
.B 0
shows the startup prompt and exits after submit or cancel.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sqlite-db " " \fIPATH\fR
Set the storage target.  If
.I PATH
is a file path, it is used as the SQLite database.  If
.I PATH
is an existing directory, or ends with a slash, records are appended to daily
log files named
.IR yyyy-mm-dd.log .
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and license information and exit successfully.
.SH KEYBOARD
.TP
.B Enter
Submit the current prompt.  If the activity field is empty after trimming, no
record is saved.
.TP
.B Escape
Cancel the current prompt without saving.  Three consecutive Escape cancels
exit the application.
.TP
.B Control-S
Snooze the prompt for 30 seconds.
.TP
.B Control-Q
Quit the application from the prompt.
.TP
.B Mod4-Alt-G
Show the prompt immediately while the application is waiting.  Mod4 is usually
the Windows or Super key.  This shortcut is registered through X11 on Linux.
.TP
.B Quit
Click the small Quit label in the prompt footer to exit the application.
.TP
.BR F1 ", " F2
Decrease or increase the energy score by half a step.
.TP
.BR F3 ", " F4
Decrease or increase the mood score by half a step.
.TP
.BR F5 ", " F6
Decrease or increase the grounding score by half a step.
.SH STORAGE
.SS SQLite
The SQLite table is created automatically:
.PP
.nf
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS observations (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
    energy REAL,
    mood REAL,
    grounding REAL,
    activity TEXT NOT NULL,
    quote TEXT
);
.fi
.PP
Default scores are treated as unrecorded values and are stored as
.BR NULL .
.SS Directory logs
Directory logging writes one file per day.  A record looks like:
.PP
.nf
hh:mm:ss e2.5 m3.5 g4.0
    activity text
.fi
.PP
Score fields that remain at the default value are omitted.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid command-line options or runtime errors during startup.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
